.TH XLLMNRD 8 2013-11-28 "@PACKAGE_STRING@"
.SH NAME
xllmnrd \- IPv6 LLMNR responder
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY xllmnrd
.OP \-f
.OP \-n name
.OP \-\-foreground
.RB [ \-\-name=\fIname\fB ]
.SY xllmnrd
.B \-\-help
.SY xllmnrd
.B \-\-version
.YS
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B xllmnrd
program responds to Link-Local Multicast Name Resolution (LLMNR) queries
for the host.
It normally runs in the background as a system daemon unless either
.B \-f
or
.B \-\-foreground
option is used.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-foreground
Make
.B xllmnrd
run in the foreground.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-name=\fIname\fB
Set the host name of the responder to
.IR name .
If this option is not present, the name returned from
.BR gethostname (3)
is used by default.
If the host name consists of multiple labels, only the first label is used
by the responder.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Display a short help and exit.
Any following options are silently discarded.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Output version information and exit.
Any following options are silently discarded.
.SH BUGS
The
.B xllmnrd
program currently responds always with no answer sections
and does not implement all the requirements specified in RFC 4795 yet.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gethostname (2),
.BR syslog (3),
RFC 4795.
